arts.ttl: Colchester United 1 AFC Wimbledon 1 - reaction from Danny Cowley after draw
arts.sum: Samson Tovide came off the bench to head home in the 89th minute on his comeback from injury to secure a point for the U's, who had fallen behind to Marcus Browne's first-half effort. "Our last home game was against Walsall who were top, today we played Wimbledon who are second and I thought in both games, we were the better team.

arts.ttl: Samson Tovide rescues a point for Colchester against AFC Wimbledon
arts.sum: Tovide cancelled out Marcus Browne’s first-half opener.

arts.ttl: Colchester United 1 AFC Wimbledon 1 - match report as Tovide nets late equaliser
arts.sum: AFC Wimbledon had a penalty appeal rejected when Josh Neufville tumbled under Ellis Iandolo's challenge in the area before Colchester made a double change with 15 minutes remaining, sending on Tovide and Kane Vincent-Young in a bid to find an equaliser. Colchester, wearing their black and white change kit after a shirt clash with the Dons, felt they should have had a penalty in the seventh minute when Taylor fell under the challenge of former U’s keeper Owen Goodman in the area.

arts.ttl: Colchester United v AFC Wimbledon - predicted teams, odds, all you need to know
arts.sum: Colchester United head coach Danny Cowley on AFC Wimbledon game: Colchester could welcome back striker Samson Tovide to their squad for their game against AFC Wimbledon.

arts.ttl: Kyreece Lisbie on target as Colchester United under-21s slide to heavy defeat
arts.sum: Colchester were reduced to ten players before Dixon wrapped up Charlton's win, a minute later. Charlton had a player sent off just after the hour mark but scored their sixth when a loose ball was seized upon by Enslin on 72 minutes.

arts.ttl: Danny Cowley ready for 'brilliant test' for Colchester side against Wimbledon
arts.sum: But they face a Wimbledon side who themselves are flying, with Johnnie Jackson's team having embarked on an 11-match unbeaten sequence in League Two as they chase automatic promotion. “They’re a very, very good team and have all of the tools to be successful in League Two and I anticipate them to be promoted automatically, come the end of the season."

arts.ttl: Danny Cowley: continuity and rhythm fuelling Colchester United's unbeaten run
arts.sum: "It's such a tactical game, I didn't want to throw boys in (against Notts County), that hadn't played together because I didn't think that was fair on them. Colchester extended their unbeaten run in midweek with a creditable 1-1 draw at promotion-chasing Notts County, barely 72 hours after their 630-mile round trip to Carlisle United.
